  "date": "2025-09-02",
  "summary_en": "In this humorous but thought-provoking post, the author presents a speculative scenario in which evolution ('the cat shoggoth') has aligned humans' utility functions toward cat well-being. It argues that human-cat relations are an existing attractor for coherent extrapolated volition (CEV), suggesting that if we can align intelligences to care about cats, that alignment could scale. The author proposes a concrete plan: recreating pre-domestication cat populations, using AI to guard grain warehouses etc., so as to provide a process for learning the cat utility function from data, thereby making progress in AI alignment.",
  "summary_zh": "这篇带有幽默色彩但发人深省的文章提出一个假设：进化（“猫之 shoggoth”）已经使人类的效用函数朝向关爱猫类的方向对齐。作者认为人与猫的关系是“相干外推意志”（CEV）的一个既存吸引子，并暗示若我们能使更高阶智能体关心猫，那么这种对齐有可能可扩展。文章提出一个具体方案：重建驯化前猫的种群，使用 AI 保护储粮仓免受老鼠侵害等，以此从数据中学习猫的效用函数，从而在 AI 对齐问题上取得进展。",
  "best_quote_en": "Evolutionary pressure is an intelligence we need to model, and pretending that it doesn't move with intentionality makes the world unnecessarily hard to understand.",
  "best_quote_zh": "进化压力是我们需要建模的一种智能，假装它不带有意图性只会让世界变得不必要地难以理解。"
